    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>sausages </strong>to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the sausages are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sausages are cooking, peel your<strong> potatoes </strong>and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are boiling, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash, then rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a separate baking tray with a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the<strong> sliced garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the middle of the foil with a small knob of<strong> butter</strong>, a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil to form a sealed parcel and put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the greens are tender</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> </strong>the<strong> remaining sliced garlic</strong> and your <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the sauce is thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is cooking, return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-and-mash-with-garlic-tomato-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausages</strong> with the<strong> mash</strong> and <strong>spring greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon the <strong>garlic tomato sauce</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
